## 02. KEY WORKFLOW LEARNINGS (read before regenerating anything)

1. **Never chain edits.** Feeding a previously-generated image back into GPT Image 2 / Nano Banana repeatedly as an "edit base" causes visible degradation (spots, pixelation) within 2-3 passes. Always generate **fresh** from clean original reference images + a full text description. If a fix is needed, restate the full scene from scratch rather than editing on top.
2. **Soul 2.0** (`soul_id`) reliably locks face identity but handles complex wardrobe/scene composition poorly — outputs look "off."
3. **Nano Banana Pro / Nano Banana 2** respects `<<<element_id>>>` for wardrobe/car well but does **not** reliably hold a Soul-locked face — it tends to regenerate its own face even when a Soul character is referenced.
4. **GPT Image 2** (`gpt_image_2`) is the most reliable model for this pipeline. It follows long, explicit, itemized prompts precisely — labeling each input image ("Image 1 = face ref," "Image 2 = eye-color ref," "Image 3 = scene ref") and spelling out details in full sentences (exact heterochromia per eye, "North Asian mixed-race," "lips fully closed," etc.) gets the most accurate results. Use `quality: "high"`, `resolution: "4k"`.
5. Getting the face to read as **North Asian** (not generic Asian, not Western, not African) required explicitly naming Mongolian/Northern Chinese bone structure, high wide cheekbones, Mongolian fold, broad flat facial planes — generic "Asian" prompting drifted away from this.
6. Getting a **seamless yellow ganzfeld background** (no lines/seams/corners) required explicitly banning "lines, seams, corners, architectural details" and describing it as an "infinite glowing yellow void."

